---
title: Balsamic Rosemary Strip Steak with Garlic Herb Toasts and a Roasted Apple Salad
description: Balsamic vinegar does multiple magnificent things in this recipe. First, it’s stirred into the sauce to give it an acidity that cuts through and livens up the robust flavor of the steak. Then, it’s tossed into an apple-topped arugula salad, providing a rounded contrast to the sweetness of the fruit. Even the baguette toasts on the side, brushed in a garlic herb butter, are great for sopping up all that flavor.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/balsamic-rosemary-strip-steak-60c7cdae.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/balsamic-rosemary-strip-steak-5abd497aae08b54b9a2484a2-69dea28b.pdf
course: main course
cuisine: North America
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/balsamic-rosemary-strip-steak-5abd497aae08b54b9a2484a2
time required: 45 minutes
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 970 kcal
  fat: 56 g
  saturated fat: 21 g
  carbohydrates: 72 g
  sugar: 24 g
  protein: 49 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 1180 mg
author: Sara Heilman
---

Wash and dry all produce. Adjust rack to middle position and preheat #oven{} to 400 degrees. Cut one @Demi-Baguette{1} into ½-inch cubes. Halve and core @Apple{1}; cut into ½-inch wedges. Place baguette cubes and apple on opposite sides of a foil-lined #baking sheet{}. Toss each with @salt{}, @Pepper{}, and a drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{2%tsp}. Bake until baguette is crisp, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve, peel, and thinly slice @Shallot{2}. Pick and finely chop enough @Rosemary{¼%ounce} leaves from stems to give you 2 tsp. Split remaining @Demi-Baguette{1} in half. Place @Garlic Herb Butter{2%tbsp} in a #small bowl{} and microwave on high until melted, about ~{30%seconds}. Drizzle over baguette halves.

Once apple and baguette cubes have baked ~{8-10%minutes}, remove cubes from baking sheet and set aside. Flip apple and continue baking until browned, another ~{10-15%minutes}. Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Season @New York Strip Steak{12%ounce} all over with salt and pepper. Add to pan and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Remove steak from pan and set aside to rest. Lower heat to medium and heat a drizzle of oil in same pan. Add shallots and cook, tossing, until lightly browned, ~{5-7%minutes}. Add chopped rosemary and cook until fragrant, about ~{30%seconds}. Stir in @water{½%cup}, @Balsamic Vinegar{1%tsp} (we'll use more of it later), and @Chicken Demi-Glace{1}.scrape up any browned bits on bottom. Simmer until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with pepper.

While shallots cook, place buttered baguette halves cut-side up on another baking sheet. Toast in oven until golden brown, ~{6-7%minutes}. Meanwhile, toss @Arugula{2%ounce}, baguette cubes, @Balsamic Vinegar{2%tsp}, and @Olive Oil{1%tbsp} in a #medium bowl{}. Season with salt and pepper.

Slice steak against the grain. Divide steak, salad, and garlic bread between plates. Drizzle sauce over steak. Top salad with apple and crumble @Ricotta Salata Cheese{2%ounce} over.

> Balsamic vinegar does multiple magnificent things in this recipe. It cuts through and livens up the robust flavor of the steak, provides a rounded contrast to the sweetness of the fruit in the salad, and the garlic herb butter toasts are great for sopping up all that flavor.